definitions.definition: Not lying on a straight line .
Whose atoms do not lie in a straight line.
Having a product of independent variables, or a variable with an exponent not equal to one.
Whose output is not directly proportional to its input .
Erratic and unpredictable ; tending to jump back and forth.
examples: a film with a nonlinear plot

main_definition: ( of a set of points ) Not lying on a straight line .
secondary_definitions: ( chemistry , of a molecule ) Whose atoms do not lie in a straight line.
( mathematics , of a function ) Having a product of independent variables, or a variable with an exponent not equal to one.
( of a system ) Whose output is not directly proportional to its input .
Erratic and unpredictable ; tending to jump back and forth.
